cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.CR, cs.CL 

This paper analyzes the behavior of state-sponsored trolls on Twitter and their influence on the information ecosystem, which falls under the categories of social media analysis (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses disinformation and manipulation on the web, which could be categorized under cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses statistical modeling to quantify the influence of these trolls, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
